description.narrative: By the end of 2020, over 500,000 people in the five UNICEF supported focus districts have improved availability of and increased demand for high impact maternal, new-born and child health interventions., which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, reduced child mortality and under-nutrition through improved and equitable use of high impact health, nutrition and WASH interventions.

description.narrative: In 2020, the Health program centered on COVID-19 response. UNICEF played pivotal roles in supporting the Ministry of Health (MOH) for COVID-19 response through provision of medical equipment and infection and prevention control supplies, monitoring, technical assistance and capacity building of health workers. UNICEF is supporting the MOH to prepare for COVID-19 vaccine deployment planned for mid-2021. UNICEF supported MOH to maintain primary health care services during COVID-19 pandemic. 46,212 children were immunized against bOPV/DT-5 through catch-up campaigns. Health promotion has been key to strengthening the health seeking behavior for MNCH and immunization services. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:03/02/2021
